    <IRS990ScheduleO documentId="990xScheduleO">
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>Schedule O:</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>Part I.10 Girls Tuition Assistance to South Sudanese Girls $ 46,272 Grants to Girls With Books! associated with liquidation/merger $ 97,417 Part 1.16 Other expenses Outside computer services: $ 1189 Insurance: $ 315 State Annual Registration: $10 Refund of bank/merchant charges: $(145) TOTAL: $ 1369 Part 2.26 Total liabilities: $577 Outstanding credit card balance from prior year balance sheet Part 5.34 On Sept. 20, 2023, the Board of Directors of Project Education Sudan (PES) unanimously resolved to dissolve PES, effective Sept. 30, 2023, as reflected in the Notice of Dissolution filed with the Colorado Secretary of State, which is attached. This resolution and dissolution followed PES resolutions adopted a year earlier, on Sept. 9, 2022, in which the Board of Directors of PES resolved to merge its operations as of Oct. 1, 2022 with Empowerment Through Education Foundation (ETE), a Colorado non-profit organization, which is a 501 (c)(3) organization with the same mission as PES. These 2022 resolutions provided that ETE would file a name change with the Colorado Secretary of State to Girls With Books!, and that the merged corporation would operate under that name. The resolutions further provided that PES would continue to exist for the purpose of winding down certain independent operations in 2023 and that its remaining funds would be transferred to Girls With Books!. In accordance with these resolutions, PES has wound down its independent operations and transferred its remaining funds in the amount of $97,417 to Girls With Books! for the purpose of furthering the mission of Girls With Books! to support its work to educate South Sudanese girls.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
    </IRS990ScheduleO>
